INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '606873b7-140b-4194-beaa-1fea8d33c87e',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Rust in Production — Runtime Metrics, Async Profiling, and Allocator Pressure$escape$,
  $escape$Rust has no GC, so GC pauses are off the table — but allocator latency and async executor stalls are real production concerns. The `metrics` crate provides a zero-cost abstraction facade: instrument library code with `counter!`, `gauge!`, and `histogram!` macros, then swap in `metrics-exporter-prometheus` at the binary layer with no library changes. For Tokio workloads, `tokio-metrics` exposes `TaskMonitor` — wrap any `Future` to collect `mean_poll_duration`, `slow_poll_ratio`, and `dropped_count` per interval. Slow polls (>500µs) signal tasks blocking the executor thread via sync I/O or CPU-heavy work. Use `tokio-console` (set `TOKIO_CONSOLE=1`, add `console-subscriber`) for live terminal introspection without code changes. For CPU flamegraphs in production, `pprof-rs` integrates with signal-based sampling and emits SVGs or protobuf profiles compatible with `go tool pprof` — expose a `/debug/pprof` endpoint gated behind middleware auth. For allocator pressure, swap to `tikv-jemallocator` as your `#[global_allocator]` and poll its stats API to track arena fragmentation ratios.$escape$,
  $escape$use tokio_metrics::TaskMonitor;
use std::time::Duration;

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() {
    let monitor = TaskMonitor::new();

    tokio::spawn({
        let monitor = monitor.clone();
        async move {
            for interval in monitor.intervals() {
                println!("mean_poll: {:?}", interval.mean_poll_duration);
                println!("slow_poll_ratio: {:.4}", interval.slow_poll_ratio);
                println!("dropped: {}", interval.dropped_count);
                tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_secs(5)).await;
            }
        }
    });

    monitor.instrument(do_work()).await;
}

async fn do_work() {
    tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_millis(120)).await;
}$escape$,
  $escape$rust$escape$,
